00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:13.263 position:50% align:center
[ZABURN]
Scale Mail Transformation!

00:00:13.346 --> 00:00:15.348 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR A] Zaburn,
the Emperor of the Sea,

00:00:15.432 --> 00:00:17.350 position:50% align:center
has appeared to wash
away the wrongdoers

00:00:17.434 --> 00:00:21.021 position:50% align:center
in a tsunami of justice,
and flood the world with truth.

00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:22.897 position:50% align:center
Overcoming all adversity!

00:00:22.981 --> 00:00:25.442 position:50% align:center
A gargantuan sea
creature draws near!

00:00:25.525 --> 00:00:28.361 position:50% align:center
Quick! Combine! Emperor...

00:00:28.445 --> 00:00:31.114 position:50% align:center
[ZABURN]
Zaburn!

00:00:31.197 --> 00:00:32.198 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR A]
A new series...

00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:33.575 position:50% align:center
He's just as epic
no matter how much

00:00:33.658 --> 00:00:35.785 position:50% align:center
I rewatch this thing!

00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:37.620 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Gimme a break.

00:00:37.704 --> 00:00:41.041 position:50% align:center
How many times have
you replayed that?

00:00:41.124 --> 00:00:42.542 position:50% align:center
It's all I have.

00:00:42.625 --> 00:00:45.462 position:50% align:center
The <i>Zaburn</i> series
originally streamed online,

00:00:45.545 --> 00:00:49.632 position:50% align:center
and due to the catastrophe,
never got a physical release.

00:00:49.716 --> 00:00:52.385 position:50% align:center
I keep watching the same
commercial over and over

00:00:52.469 --> 00:00:55.347 position:50% align:center
because it's the
only thing available.

00:00:57.474 --> 00:00:59.142 position:50% align:center
Look! Check this baby out!

00:00:59.225 --> 00:01:01.728 position:50% align:center
Isn't the fin on his
helmet super cool?

00:01:01.811 --> 00:01:04.647 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Mhm. About as cool as a sunfish.

00:01:04.731 --> 00:01:05.815 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:09.152 position:50% align:center
[RIN] Hello! It's
obviously a shark fin!

00:01:09.235 --> 00:01:10.445 position:50% align:center
Well, sunfish or not,

00:01:10.528 --> 00:01:12.781 position:50% align:center
this seems like a silly
boys' hobby to me.

00:01:12.864 --> 00:01:15.075 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Ah! Stereotype much?

00:01:15.158 --> 00:01:16.868 position:50% align:center
You act so sweet
in front of your fans,

00:01:16.951 --> 00:01:18.912 position:50% align:center
but you're so mean
behind the scenes!

00:01:18.995 --> 00:01:22.791 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] That was the old me. I'm
done being a superficial idol.

00:01:22.874 --> 00:01:24.751 position:50% align:center
Plus, it's unhealthy to
constantly worry about

00:01:24.834 --> 00:01:26.461 position:50% align:center
what everyone thinks of you.

00:01:26.544 --> 00:01:29.130 position:50% align:center
My shoulders are as stiff
as a board, Hosomichi.

00:01:29.214 --> 00:01:30.840 position:50% align:center
Give me a massage.

00:01:30.924 --> 00:01:34.010 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
'Kay, I will in a bit.

00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:36.930 position:50% align:center
How can you agree to
something that's so indecent?

00:01:37.013 --> 00:01:39.516 position:50% align:center
Because managers
love pleasing idols.

00:01:39.599 --> 00:01:41.893 position:50% align:center
Hey, have this talk away
from an open flame.

00:01:41.976 --> 00:01:43.269 position:50% align:center
That isn't fair!

00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:45.939 position:50% align:center
You said you were my partner
before you ever met her!

00:01:46.022 --> 00:01:47.190 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Hmm?

00:01:47.273 --> 00:01:49.109 position:50% align:center
You two-timer.

00:01:49.192 --> 00:01:50.443 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Ha-ha.

00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:52.487 position:50% align:center
[RIN] It's not funny!
Why are you laughing?

00:01:52.570 --> 00:01:56.324 position:50% align:center
You really thought of me as some
sidepiece this whole time?

00:01:56.408 --> 00:01:59.703 position:50% align:center
Rin, don't dive headfirst
into wrong conclusions.

00:02:01.037 --> 00:02:02.163 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:04.791 position:50% align:center
Stop petting me like
I'm some kind of puppy!

00:02:06.418 --> 00:02:09.087 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Let's dig in!

00:02:09.170 --> 00:02:10.296 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
You two should rest up and eat

00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:13.091 position:50% align:center
while you have the chance.

00:02:13.174 --> 00:02:15.510 position:50% align:center
Who knows when we'll have
to operate the robot again,

00:02:15.593 --> 00:02:17.595 position:50% align:center
so best be ready for whenever.

00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:19.264 position:50% align:center
It's a Garanndoll.

00:02:19.347 --> 00:02:21.474 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Yeah, that thing.

00:02:23.435 --> 00:02:24.519 position:50% align:center
You're doin' pretty well

00:02:24.602 --> 00:02:28.314 position:50% align:center
considering how much
you gripe and groan.

00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:30.483 position:50% align:center
As a pilot, I mean.

00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:34.487 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI] Not everyone
likes the jobs they have.

00:02:36.489 --> 00:02:37.866 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
At least it pays.

00:02:37.949 --> 00:02:40.035 position:50% align:center
But passion powers Shark One.

00:02:40.118 --> 00:02:43.163 position:50% align:center
You have to enjoy
it to some extent.

00:02:43.246 --> 00:02:46.249 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI] That's what makes
that robot so annoying.

00:02:46.332 --> 00:02:47.917 position:50% align:center
It's called a Garanndoll!

00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:50.587 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Yeah, that thing.

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.131 position:50% align:center
[MUNAKATA] Well, aren't you
three getting along swimmingly.

00:02:53.214 --> 00:02:54.215 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Why are you here?

00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.759 position:50% align:center
Because.

00:04:28.893 --> 00:04:29.894 position:50% align:center
[MUNAKATA]
By the look of things,

00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:32.772 position:50% align:center
I'd say you've got
your groove back.

00:04:32.856 --> 00:04:34.024 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
You think?

00:04:34.107 --> 00:04:36.192 position:50% align:center
For your sake, I sure hope so.

00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:39.237 position:50% align:center
You need the mojo to make the
money to pay off your debt.

00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:41.489 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI grunts]

00:04:41.573 --> 00:04:42.782 position:50% align:center
Hey, could be worse.

00:04:42.866 --> 00:04:44.784 position:50% align:center
You might wanna
count your blessings.

00:04:44.868 --> 00:04:46.453 position:50% align:center
I'd hate to stuff
you in an oil drum

00:04:46.536 --> 00:04:49.622 position:50% align:center
and dump you in
the sea of trees.

00:04:49.706 --> 00:04:51.291 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
Yeah, I hear you.

00:04:51.374 --> 00:04:55.378 position:50% align:center
Boys! Secret secrets are no fun.

00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:58.340 position:50% align:center
Hey. We're just
shooting the breeze.

00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:01.885 position:50% align:center
Oh, actually, I have a
message for you guys.

00:05:01.968 --> 00:05:04.179 position:50% align:center
Mimi wants you at the
command center, ASAP.

00:05:04.262 --> 00:05:06.639 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Why are we reporting for?

00:05:09.476 --> 00:05:12.312 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC] Behold! A film of
the enemy's propaganda.

00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:14.939 position:50% align:center
One that Ukai risked
his life to obtain.

00:05:15.023 --> 00:05:17.233 position:50% align:center
[RIN] So, it shows what life
in their country is like?

00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:18.610 position:50% align:center
This should be very enlightening

00:05:18.693 --> 00:05:20.612 position:50% align:center
since we've all been
in the dark about that.

00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:23.740 position:50% align:center
[CAP] Could even teach us how
to exploit their weaknesses.

00:05:23.823 --> 00:05:25.241 position:50% align:center
Enough chitchat, everyone.

00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:27.243 position:50% align:center
Take a seat and
we'll get started.

00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:29.954 position:50% align:center
Here, Hosomichi,
I got us some popcorn!

00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:30.538 position:50% align:center
Oh.

00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:32.499 position:50% align:center
[RIN screams]

00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:36.044 position:50% align:center
[ALL shouting]

00:05:36.127 --> 00:05:36.753 position:50% align:center
[GUYS groan]

00:05:36.836 --> 00:05:38.672 position:50% align:center
[YUKI grunts]

00:05:39.714 --> 00:05:44.052 position:50% align:center
[MIMI] Quiet down. This is
important, so pay attention.

00:06:03.321 --> 00:06:06.032 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR B] While conducting
phase space energy experiments,

00:06:06.116 --> 00:06:08.326 position:50% align:center
we accidentally
uncovered something.

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:13.373 position:50% align:center
Something that can only be
described as a terrifying truth.

00:06:13.456 --> 00:06:15.667 position:50% align:center
We found the existence
of what was dubbed

00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:17.293 position:50% align:center
"an illusory country."

00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:21.715 position:50% align:center
A world that mirrors our own,
only it's a complete travesty.

00:06:21.798 --> 00:06:23.842 position:50% align:center
A mockery on the
upstanding society

00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.720 position:50% align:center
we built our Japan to be.

00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:28.930 position:50% align:center
One key difference
is how miserably

00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:32.017 position:50% align:center
this farcical Japan
lost in the world war.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:34.811 position:50% align:center
Japanese pride and spirit
is absent among their youth,

00:06:34.894 --> 00:06:36.730 position:50% align:center
while things like anime
and mobile games

00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:38.481 position:50% align:center
take precedence in their lives,

00:06:38.565 --> 00:06:40.650 position:50% align:center
poisoning their minds
and further influencing

00:06:40.734 --> 00:06:42.861 position:50% align:center
their already poor choices.

00:06:42.944 --> 00:06:45.947 position:50% align:center
Foolishness at its
finest, and its worst.

00:06:46.031 --> 00:06:49.868 position:50% align:center
A fate as regrettable
as it is deplorable.

00:06:50.994 --> 00:06:52.787 position:50% align:center
So what if it's
a parallel world?

00:06:52.871 --> 00:06:56.541 position:50% align:center
They're every bit as Japanese
as the rest of us here!

00:06:56.624 --> 00:06:58.001 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR B]
A sound conclusion reached

00:06:58.084 --> 00:07:00.503 position:50% align:center
by the military powers-that-be.

00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:02.505 position:50% align:center
They know not what they do.

00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
Therefore, it is
our responsibility

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:07.552 position:50% align:center
as the True Country to save
our brethren from themselves

00:07:07.635 --> 00:07:12.682 position:50% align:center
and guide them down
the correct path.

00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:14.726 position:50% align:center
A decade has passed since
our first encounter

00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:16.061 position:50% align:center
with the mirror world,

00:07:16.144 --> 00:07:18.938 position:50% align:center
and a third wave of troops
was recently dispatched.

00:07:19.022 --> 00:07:20.815 position:50% align:center
With elite soldiers
at his flanks,

00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:22.650 position:50% align:center
Captain Akatsuki
now paves the way

00:07:22.734 --> 00:07:26.654 position:50% align:center
as we continue our
educational endeavor.

00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:28.198 position:50% align:center
Good morning.

00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:31.368 position:50% align:center
May we use the light of a new
day to awaken their spirit.

00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:33.661 position:50% align:center
It's slept too long.

00:07:33.745 --> 00:07:35.497 position:50% align:center
Being raised with
a defeated mentality

00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:38.083 position:50% align:center
has made them
dependent on nonsense.

00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.585 position:50% align:center
Sadly, they've had their
futures stolen from them,

00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:42.504 position:50% align:center
yet they're oblivious to it all.

00:07:42.587 --> 00:07:45.048 position:50% align:center
That's why it falls upon
us to help them out.

00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:48.176 position:50% align:center
It's our duty to take their
hands and unify our worlds.

00:07:48.259 --> 00:07:50.804 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:52.597 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR B] The cherry
blossoms are in bloom,

00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:55.100 position:50% align:center
and the people can't help but
hope our country will flourish

00:07:55.183 --> 00:07:58.978 position:50% align:center
just as beautifully with Captain
Akatsuki taking charge.

00:07:59.062 --> 00:08:03.900 position:50% align:center
This broadcast was brought
to you by our military HQ.

00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:14.327 position:50% align:center
Uhh... What the actual hell?

00:08:14.411 --> 00:08:15.829 position:50% align:center
Wow.

00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.373 position:50% align:center
A Japan that managed to pull
off a win for the world war.

00:08:18.456 --> 00:08:20.125 position:50% align:center
Thanks for the nightmare fuel.

00:08:20.208 --> 00:08:21.543 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:08:21.626 --> 00:08:22.836 position:50% align:center
Makes no nevermind to me

00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:25.046 position:50% align:center
if there's a second
Japan in existence.

00:08:25.130 --> 00:08:27.549 position:50% align:center
I find it intriguing,
exciting, even!

00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:29.509 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:31.386 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Those jerks.

00:08:31.469 --> 00:08:34.222 position:50% align:center
What right do they have
to censor innocent idols?

00:08:34.305 --> 00:08:37.100 position:50% align:center
We are entertainers,
not criminals!

00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:39.728 position:50% align:center
I feel the same way
about anime and manga.

00:08:39.811 --> 00:08:40.729 position:50% align:center
They chose to cancel them

00:08:40.812 --> 00:08:42.689 position:50% align:center
without even giving
them a chance!

00:08:42.772 --> 00:08:44.024 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
This is just the first step

00:08:44.107 --> 00:08:46.026 position:50% align:center
of their great
cultural invasion.

00:08:46.109 --> 00:08:49.112 position:50% align:center
If we submit and accept
their rigorous terms,

00:08:49.195 --> 00:08:51.281 position:50% align:center
it will be the end of our
lives as we know them

00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:54.701 position:50% align:center
and the beginning of a
relentless martial law!

00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:58.204 position:50% align:center
Right, it's like we're a dam!

00:08:58.288 --> 00:08:59.622 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Close.

00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:03.918 position:50% align:center
I'm more partial to the phrase
"last line of defense."

00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:05.295 position:50% align:center
[RIN squeals]

00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:06.880 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
I just got chills!

00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:07.964 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:08.798 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
We're gonna save the world...

00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:10.300 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
What's eating you?

00:09:10.383 --> 00:09:13.470 position:50% align:center
I dunno. Just not sure
I'm on the right side.

00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:15.138 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Huh?

00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:16.181 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Hm?

00:09:16.264 --> 00:09:17.349 position:50% align:center
The heck's that mean?!

00:09:17.432 --> 00:09:18.975 position:50% align:center
You're saying you
support boring people

00:09:19.059 --> 00:09:21.603 position:50% align:center
enforcing their boring ways
on more cultured minds?

00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:24.272 position:50% align:center
They hate what we love!
It's not right!

00:09:24.356 --> 00:09:26.483 position:50% align:center
It's tough,
but think logically.

00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:29.277 position:50% align:center
The True Army is already
occupying our country.

00:09:29.361 --> 00:09:32.572 position:50% align:center
When push came to shove, we
just let them walk on through.

00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:35.950 position:50% align:center
That kinda speaks to
where most people stand.

00:09:36.034 --> 00:09:37.285 position:50% align:center
Huh? Ah!

00:09:37.369 --> 00:09:38.912 position:50% align:center
Don't spew that garbage here.

00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:41.498 position:50% align:center
You some kinda True Army
sympathizer, or what?

00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:42.957 position:50% align:center
You didn't let me
finish, big guy!

00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:45.794 position:50% align:center
So, please, put that thing away.

00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:50.590 position:50% align:center
No, I see the point you were
trying to make, 100%, but still.

00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:52.217 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC]
Mimi.

00:09:53.134 --> 00:09:57.806 position:50% align:center
I think I should be the one
to handle this. Understood?

00:10:00.141 --> 00:10:01.726 position:50% align:center
[UKAI]
Tch.

00:10:02.686 --> 00:10:05.438 position:50% align:center
[ALL sigh]

00:10:05.522 --> 00:10:06.815 position:50% align:center
I swear.

00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:08.066 position:50% align:center
So not cool.

00:10:08.149 --> 00:10:09.943 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
What?

00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:12.278 position:50% align:center
[BALZAC] I'm glad we
could have this talk.

00:10:12.362 --> 00:10:14.781 position:50% align:center
You're all dismissed.

00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:16.282 position:50% align:center
[YUKI groans]

00:10:16.366 --> 00:10:18.368 position:50% align:center
Dealing with idiots really does
a number on my shoulders,

00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:21.162 position:50% align:center
so I'm gonna go enjoy
a long, luxurious bath.

00:10:21.246 --> 00:10:23.707 position:50% align:center
[MIMI] Oh. Would you
mind if I joined you?

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:26.251 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Not at all.
You come, too, Rin.

00:10:26.334 --> 00:10:28.545 position:50% align:center
Uh, okay.

00:10:30.296 --> 00:10:32.716 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Today would be nice!

00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:38.805 position:50% align:center
[door closes]

00:10:45.478 --> 00:10:47.605 position:50% align:center
[HOSOMICHI]
What did I do?

00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:55.655 position:50% align:center
[AKATSUKI]
Yes.

00:10:55.739 --> 00:10:57.907 position:50% align:center
Insist that Kabukicho is
nothing but a pile of ash now

00:10:57.991 --> 00:11:00.535 position:50% align:center
because the rebels
chose to resist.

00:11:01.578 --> 00:11:02.662 position:50% align:center
Take care not to offend

00:11:02.746 --> 00:11:04.706 position:50% align:center
their country's prime
minister, please.

00:11:04.789 --> 00:11:06.332 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER A]
Yes, sir!

00:11:08.877 --> 00:11:12.839 position:50% align:center
So easy to quell their
complaints, almost too easy.

00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:14.591 position:50% align:center
[MUSASHI] The smart and
merciful thing to do

00:11:14.674 --> 00:11:16.676 position:50% align:center
would simply be to purge them.

00:11:16.760 --> 00:11:19.554 position:50% align:center
Force alone can't
inspire patriotism.

00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:21.556 position:50% align:center
They have to come
meet us halfway.

00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:24.017 position:50% align:center
If they don't wish to
understand our philosophy,

00:11:24.100 --> 00:11:26.936 position:50% align:center
we can never be comrades
who share the same future.

00:11:27.020 --> 00:11:28.563 position:50% align:center
